spanGrp.span: There was big child walking in the bush;
Peyaba kipashkeka dam shk-g k'yaka n ska
That big bear teaches him how to look for and eat ants.
Je oso t' t jie kashe-g mnbi mnbi sawak yule-s' sawak kt-gl w
He gives him a ripe banana to eat;
he teaches him how to dance;
[and teaches him] how to walk on branches,
how to scratch oneself with sticks and stones.
mnbi mnbi jk pabi kal m jak m
There comes a big tiger who looked after the child;
Jeska nm nm nm dam je t je peyaba knn-ra-m
maybe he wanted to devour him,
but since the child was accompanied by the bear, he could not devour him.
Pero komo peyaba dula-m r oso ra je kueinga ka ka mnbi ka katan-w
There the child looked after him;
the big bear was playing with the child,
Jeska ra oso t' jin-g peyaba ra
he only wanted to eat ripe bananas.
y solamente jen r chomli b n bi -ite bi -ite
Next, there was a stone; he put the child under it to look for ants to eat.
Jeska ra jak/ peyaba pakke-g-w-ite jak jak blan sawak yl kete-ite
There the stone rolled down but the child was already out and so did not die.
Jeska ra jak bt-g-te-ra peyaba des-ka-n Ka ka dun-w jak
There they walked under the branches, looking for bananas.
Jeska mi-gu-lo-m shk kaljula jrga chomli yl jk
Then he scratches himself using things that grow by the river.
pabiu-g jir ts tbi-l digl km ska kal m jir m
In the branches the tiger was going after them, looking at them; the tiger went behind him, taking care of him.
(_) nm dam jie jie s tinga nm t tjie-ra-m knn-ra-m
They went to bathe and fell in a small river;
Jeska m-gu-lo-m jug jr-g-s' diglyaba inga
The child jumped as the big bear did.
yaba jk bu-g-m mnbi oso t' t jir wable-g bi
he did as told by the bear,
yaba t we-g-n mnbi je t pakte-g-ite (_)
"Do it like this; do it like this!
They went onto the river and played in it.
Jeska jie dam je ra digl inga jie-wa jin-ra-m jie-wa jin-ra-m digl inga
And the tiger was looking after him.
